properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 17 at 6:06PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...Observed flooding changed from Minor to Moderate severity for the
following rivers in Michigan...Wisconsin...

Menominee River near Pembine affecting Menominee and Marinette
Counties.

The Flood Warning continues for
the Menominee River near Pembine.
* Until further notice.
* At 5:00 PM CST Monday the stage was 17.4 feet.
* Flood stage is 15.0 feet.
* Moderate flooding is occurring. This approaches the flood of
record.
* Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending
at 5:00 PM CST Monday was 17.5 feet.
* Forecast...No forecast is available for this location.
* Impact...At 16.9 feet, Cold conditions and above normal flows in
the winter continue to create ice jams downstream of the Pemene
Falls. Water and ice levels fluctuate during ice jams. Please
report any observations of ice jams to your local law enforcement
agency to relay to the National Weather Service.
* Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 16.2
feet on 01/30/1993.
properties.instruction:
Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks.

Additional information is available at www.weather.gov.

The next statement will be issued Tuesday morning at 615 AM CST.

NWSheadline: Observed flooding increased from Minor to Moderate severity
